00:44:51,150 --> 00:44:54,950
Very funny. Come on.
Do what you used to do to me.

734
00:44:55,070 --> 00:44:57,750
- What would that be?
- You know.

735
00:45:00,630 --> 00:45:02,030
- You never do that anymore.
- I do.

736
00:45:02,150 --> 00:45:03,270
- No, you don't.
- I don't?

737
00:45:03,390 --> 00:45:04,910
You don't. Just do it!

738
00:45:05,550 --> 00:45:07,870
- Now?
- Yes! Now.

739
00:45:10,390 --> 00:45:13,510
- I'll finish this, then I'm taking a break.
- You sleeping with her?

740
00:45:13,590 --> 00:45:14,830
- You sleeping with my wife?
- No.

741
00:45:14,910 --> 00:45:16,390
- That's not what she said.
- I'm not.

742
00:45:16,510 --> 00:45:17,430
- You're lying.
- I'm not.

743
00:45:17,550 --> 00:45:18,990
- Are you sure?
- I'm sure.

744
00:45:19,070 --> 00:45:22,230
How come she's so preoccupied with you?
Totally. What are you doing?

745
00:45:22,310 --> 00:45:23,910
You hunting down the women in my life?

746
00:45:24,030 --> 00:45:28,630
Billy, listen. She calls me, all right?
She calls me, just to talk to me.

747
00:45:28,790 --> 00:45:29,710
All right.

748
00:45:30,390 --> 00:45:32,830
You're right.
What would you be sleeping with her for?

749
00:45:32,950 --> 00:45:34,310
You're right. Okay.

750
00:45:34,430 --> 00:45:36,750
I'm gonna tell you something.
I'm gonna tell you once.

751
00:45:36,830 --> 00:45:39,670
Don't talk to my wife, all right?
If she calls, you hang up.

752
00:45:39,750 --> 00:45:41,790
You're filling her head with shit about love...

753
00:45:41,910 --> 00:45:43,510
...and manifesting your own destiny.

754
00:45:43,630 --> 00:45:46,910
She's talking about going back
to that half-wit marriage counselor again.

755
00:45:47,030 --> 00:45:48,670
Maybe you should go.

756
00:45:49,950 --> 00:45:52,550
- What did you just say?
- Maybe you should go.

757
00:45:52,670 --> 00:45:55,750
That is easy for you to say,
because you're not married to her.

758
00:45:55,870 --> 00:45:58,390
Do me a favor. Please stay out of my life.

759
00:45:58,550 --> 00:46:00,310
Stay out of my sister's life, too.

760
00:46:00,390 --> 00:46:01,670
- Nina?
- No, not Nina. Anna.

761
00:46:01,790 --> 00:46:03,590
You think we're all blind?

762
00:46:03,710 --> 00:46:06,710
She's too polite to say you're a fool,
but I am not.

763
00:46:06,790 --> 00:46:08,350
You are making an ass of yourself.

764
00:46:08,470 --> 00:46:09,390
You okay, Danny?

765
00:46:09,510 --> 00:46:11,950
Don't worry.
I'm not gonna hurt him. I'm a doctor.

766
00:46:12,030 --> 00:46:14,390
I got triple-bypass surgery in 20 minutes.

767
00:46:14,510 --> 00:46:18,710
No one in my family likes you,
except my mom, 'cause she's crazy...

768
00:46:18,790 --> 00:46:20,790
...and Nina, 'cause she's blind.

769
00:46:20,910 --> 00:46:22,430
Switch me over to OR.

770
00:46:22,550 --> 00:46:25,390
If they let you glom onto them,
that's their problem.

771
00:46:25,470 --> 00:46:28,350
But whatever you do, you stay away from Irene.

772
00:46:30,230 --> 00:46:34,510
This is Dr. Swan. Can you prep Mr. Stanton?
I'll be there in about 20 minutes.

773
00:46:50,630 --> 00:46:52,630
In love, that's all you need.

774
00:46:53,470 --> 00:46:56,310
- Money. I know.
- No, not money. Show him.

775
00:46:56,430 --> 00:46:59,070
See? The coin with two heads.

776
00:46:59,710 --> 00:47:01,670
Your lady says she doesn't want to make love...

777
00:47:01,790 --> 00:47:04,030
...so you say, "We let fate decide. "

778
00:47:04,150 --> 00:47:05,590
Women love fate.

779
00:47:07,070 --> 00:47:09,630
- Is that right?
- Heads, we make love.

780
00:47:09,750 --> 00:47:12,110
Tails, I go away and don't bother you again.

781
00:47:13,190 --> 00:47:14,470
You're saying I should cheat?

782
00:47:15,390 --> 00:47:16,870
What do you mean, cheat?

783
00:47:16,990 --> 00:47:17,910
Cheat.

784
00:47:18,230 --> 00:47:21,230
You know, cheat, trick, swindle, dupe.
I couldn't do that.

785
00:47:21,310 --> 00:47:22,270
Why not?

786
00:47:22,390 --> 00:47:25,150
Because there are some things
that either work or don't work.

787
00:47:25,270 --> 00:47:26,710
You can't make it work.

788
00:47:26,830 --> 00:47:29,550
It's chemistry. I prefer to take chances.

789
00:47:34,630 --> 00:47:35,990
Give me the coin.

790
00:47:37,870 --> 00:47:39,110
Thank you.

791
00:47:45,470 --> 00:47:47,070
<i>"As anticipated...</i>

792
00:47:47,190 --> 00:47:50,830
<i>"... the cream of Moscow society
had flocked to the annual ball.</i>

793
00:47:51,150 --> 00:47:54,910
"The entrance was lit by chandeliers
and decorated with flowers.

794
00:47:55,030 --> 00:47:58,310
"From the many rooms
came a murmur of excited voices.

795
00:47:58,430 --> 00:48:02,270
"As the women arranged their hair,
the band played the first waltz.

796
00:48:02,750 --> 00:48:05,150
"The whole ball was for Kitty.

797
00:48:05,790 --> 00:48:08,150
"An enchanted dream of color...

798
00:48:08,310 --> 00:48:10,030
"... sound, and movement. "

799
00:48:10,110 --> 00:48:12,790
- What was that?
- It was just some guy going to the bar.

800
00:48:12,870 --> 00:48:15,270
- I want to go home.
- No, Nina.

801
00:48:15,550 --> 00:48:17,230
This is the perfect place to read this.

802
00:48:17,310 --> 00:48:19,590
- It's exactly like in the book.
- I don't believe you.

803
00:48:19,710 --> 00:48:21,110
Okay, listen.

804
00:48:21,350 --> 00:48:25,590
"As soon as she entered the ballroom,
Kitty was asked to waltz by the best... "

805
00:48:25,670 --> 00:48:27,830
I'm not gonna dance
with either of you shitheads.

806
00:48:27,910 --> 00:48:31,310
- Who are you gonna dance with, then?
- I want to go home. I really want to.

807
00:48:31,430 --> 00:48:33,230
Just make believe you're at a ball.

808
00:48:33,310 --> 00:48:35,190
You're in Moscow, dancing the mazurka.

809
00:48:35,270 --> 00:48:37,910
- No, I don't want to dance...
- Come on, baby, dance with me.

810
00:48:38,030 --> 00:48:39,830
Me? No, I can't dance right now. Sorry.

811
00:48:39,950 --> 00:48:41,910
Look, I just want to dance with your man.

812
00:48:42,070 --> 00:48:44,430
- He's not my man.
- She's asking you to dance, dude.

813
00:48:44,590 --> 00:48:46,270
- I can't.
- You insulting my lady?

814
00:48:46,390 --> 00:48:49,110
No. I'm not insulting anybody's lady.

815
00:48:49,230 --> 00:48:51,270
If you touch him, Jose, I'll cut you!

816
00:48:53,870 --> 00:48:56,830
- All right, one dance.
- Danny, what's going on?

817
00:48:56,950 --> 00:48:58,870
- Just sit down here.
- No, don't leave me.

818
00:48:58,990 --> 00:49:02,230
I better dance. It's the mazurka.
The woman asked, I can't refuse.

819
00:49:02,350 --> 00:49:04,590
- Come on, baby.
- I'll be back in one dance.

820
00:49:04,670 --> 00:49:06,350
We'll leave after this dance.

821
00:50:03,030 --> 00:50:05,790
I saw you looking at me from across the room.

822
00:50:06,270 --> 00:50:07,510
I'm blind.

823
00:50:09,590 --> 00:50:11,470
I knew that was the reason.

824
00:50:21,110 --> 00:50:23,350
You are a beautiful lady. What is your name?

825
00:50:23,470 --> 00:50:27,670
<i>Nina. I'm named after
a character in The Seagull.</i>

826
00:50:27,750 --> 00:50:28,830
My name is Jesus.

827
00:50:28,950 --> 00:50:31,430
I was named after a bandleader in Panama City.

828
00:50:31,630 --> 00:50:34,030
- You want to dance?
- No, thank you.

829
00:50:34,150 --> 00:50:36,750
- I'm waiting for somebody.
- For me. I know. I'm here.

830
00:50:36,830 --> 00:50:38,670
No. I can't dance.

831
00:50:39,590 --> 00:50:41,830
- Everybody can dance.
- I can't.

832
00:50:42,190 --> 00:50:43,830
- Yes, you can.
- Nope.

833
00:50:44,510 --> 00:50:46,470
When the music calls to him, Jesus listens.

834
00:50:46,590 --> 00:50:48,950
It's all he can hear. Come on, I'll show you.

835
00:50:49,110 --> 00:50:50,630
It's easy.

836
00:51:47,270 --> 00:51:50,190
- Let the music move you.
- I told you I was no good.

837
00:51:50,310 --> 00:51:52,590
Who told you that? You're a great dancer.

838
00:51:53,390 --> 00:51:55,150
- I am?
- Yeah, you are.

839
00:51:55,630 --> 00:51:57,030
See? Look. You're a natural.

840
00:51:57,150 --> 00:51:58,910
- I am not.
- Yes, you are.

841
00:51:59,030 --> 00:52:02,070
Really? I don't dance very much.

842
00:52:02,430 --> 00:52:05,510
A woman who does not dance does not live.

843
00:52:06,670 --> 00:52:08,270
- Who said that?
- Me.

844
00:52:10,230 --> 00:52:11,390
Thank you very much.

845
00:52:11,510 --> 00:52:14,710
You're a beautiful woman
and a very strong dancer...

846
00:52:14,790 --> 00:52:16,430
...but I've got to go.

847
00:52:30,030 --> 00:52:33,510
- Nina. I was worried about you.
- Danny, this is Jesus.

848
00:52:33,630 --> 00:52:35,830
- He's teaching me how to dance.
- Hi, I'm Danny...

849
00:52:35,950 --> 00:52:37,150
Now I cut your throat.

850
00:52:37,270 --> 00:52:38,510
Watch out!

851
00:52:42,310 --> 00:52:45,270
- Danny, what's happening?
- Don't worry. I'll take care of you.

852
00:52:45,790 --> 00:52:47,070
He cut me!

853
00:52:56,030 --> 00:52:58,590
- I'm gonna take you home.
- No, thank you.

854
00:52:58,710 --> 00:53:00,030
My sister is coming for me.

855
00:53:00,150 --> 00:53:02,150
As soon as Danny comes,
I'll take you both home.

856
00:53:02,270 --> 00:53:05,550
- No. I'll wait for my sister.
- Nina, are you okay?

857
00:53:05,830 --> 00:53:08,150
- Yes, I'm fine.
- But you've got blood on you.

858
00:53:08,270 --> 00:53:10,710
Blood's not a big deal.
Look, this is what you do, okay?

859
00:53:10,830 --> 00:53:12,230
You take it, soak it overnight...

860
00:53:12,350 --> 00:53:14,990
...soda water, vinegar, a touch of lemon,
comes right out.

861
00:53:15,070 --> 00:53:16,230
My name is Jesus.

862
00:53:16,350 --> 00:53:17,430
My uncle's in dry cleaning.

863
00:53:17,510 --> 00:53:19,630
- This is Anna, my sister.
- Where's Danny?

864
00:53:19,710 --> 00:53:20,830
- He got stabbed.
- What?

865
00:53:20,950 --> 00:53:22,070
Hi, Anna.

866
00:53:22,510 --> 00:53:24,030
Here. I think this has sugar in it.

867
00:53:24,190 --> 00:53:25,790
- You met Jesus?
- He saved my life.

868
00:53:25,950 --> 00:53:29,030
- Thank you. I'm taking Nina home.
- No, I can take her. I got wheels.

869
00:53:29,150 --> 00:53:31,830
- Thank you, but no.
- I think Nina wants to go home with Jesus.

870
00:53:31,950 --> 00:53:33,710
Will you stay out of this? Come on, Nina.

871
00:53:33,790 --> 00:53:35,110
He offered to drive her home.

872
00:53:35,190 --> 00:53:37,550
- She's going with me.
- Excuse me.

873
00:53:37,630 --> 00:53:40,710
Will you please stop talking about me
like I'm not here?

874
00:53:40,830 --> 00:53:43,710
I am perfectly capable of deciding for myself...

875
00:53:43,830 --> 00:53:45,710
...who I'm going to go with.

876
00:53:50,110 --> 00:53:51,830
Jesus is taking me home.

877
00:54:03,870 --> 00:54:05,110
I need a lift.

878
00:54:09,590 --> 00:54:11,750
God, I just can't believe you brought her there.

879
00:54:11,870 --> 00:54:15,630
The truth of the matter is, Nina had a great time,
and you just hate that.

880
00:54:15,750 --> 00:54:18,110
No. Nina was almost killed.

881
00:54:18,230 --> 00:54:21,630
I was almost killed! Look! Nina was fine.

882
00:54:21,750 --> 00:54:24,950
I have enough responsibility
trying to keep this family functioning...

883
00:54:25,030 --> 00:54:26,230
...without you gumming it up.

884
00:54:26,350 --> 00:54:29,670
Why are you responsible
for everyone in your family?

885
00:54:29,790 --> 00:54:31,350
Because I am. All right?

886
00:54:31,510 --> 00:54:34,190
They treat you like a valet service,
you know that?

887
00:54:34,270 --> 00:54:36,030
You know what? That's life.

888
00:54:36,150 --> 00:54:38,710
Some people take responsibility,
and others don't.

889
00:54:38,790 --> 00:54:41,110
Thanks to you,
we've got Nina cruising the barrio...

890
00:54:41,190 --> 00:54:43,470
...at night with a dishwasher named Jesus.

891
00:54:43,550 --> 00:54:46,230
Yes, she is, and she's probably having fun...

892
00:54:46,350 --> 00:54:48,110
...for the first time in her life.

893
00:54:48,190 --> 00:54:52,310
Wait a second.
She's had fun before. Nina's had fun.

894
00:54:52,430 --> 00:54:55,430
Nina's had fun before. When was that?
Tell me, when was that?

895
00:54:55,550 --> 00:54:59,070
Maybe listening to your father rant on
about how love is a conspiracy.

896
00:54:59,190 --> 00:55:00,590
I know.

897
00:55:00,710 --> 00:55:03,830
Perhaps taking a page
out of Billy and Irene's guide to marriage.

898
00:55:05,670 --> 00:55:08,350
Or feeling the passion that you and Eric ooze.

899
00:55:08,470 --> 00:55:13,030
Wait a second. Eric and I have passion.
We have passion.

900
00:55:13,190 --> 00:55:17,790
- What kind of passion is that? Tell me.
- Here we go again.

901
00:55:18,110 --> 00:55:20,310
How many times have we seen this one before?

902
00:55:20,430 --> 00:55:22,790
The cowboy, the working-class lug.

903
00:55:22,870 --> 00:55:26,670
The stranger rides into town
and teaches the repressed little puritan girl...

904
00:55:26,790 --> 00:55:28,110
...how to open up.

905
00:55:28,990 --> 00:55:32,870
That is so patronizing,
not to mention clichd and inaccurate.

906
00:55:32,990 --> 00:55:36,030
- Is it?
- For your information, I've been in love.

907
00:55:36,150 --> 00:55:37,590
I am in love.

908
00:55:39,950 --> 00:55:40,910
God.

909
00:55:41,030 --> 00:55:42,630
Why do I always feel like...

910
00:55:42,750 --> 00:55:45,590
...I have to prove something to you all the time?

911
00:55:46,190 --> 00:55:48,790
I have more passion in me
than you'd know what to do with.

912
00:55:48,910 --> 00:55:50,190
I doubt it.

913
00:55:57,230 --> 00:55:59,510
You're attracted to me, aren't you?

914
00:56:01,470 --> 00:56:02,670
Admit it.

915
00:56:03,870 --> 00:56:08,150
Want to know something?
Yes. God help me, I am.

916
00:56:08,790 --> 00:56:12,470
But I'm only attracted to you
because of your attraction to me.

917
00:56:12,990 --> 00:56:15,270
- Is that bad?
- It's ludicrous.

918
00:56:15,390 --> 00:56:17,110
It's a house of cards.

919
00:56:17,430 --> 00:56:20,110
So I have no hope?

920
00:56:21,430 --> 00:56:24,110
No, you have no hope whatsoever.

921
00:56:30,270 --> 00:56:34,030
I mean, we had an interesting experience
25 years ago...

922
00:56:34,110 --> 00:56:35,390
...and we crossed paths again.

923
00:56:35,510 --> 00:56:37,270
- That's fate.
- Fate?

924
00:56:37,390 --> 00:56:38,350
Yes.

925
00:56:38,710 --> 00:56:39,630
Fate.

926
00:56:39,790 --> 00:56:42,470
Please, the last refuge of the truly desperate.

927
00:56:46,590 --> 00:56:47,830
All right.

928
00:56:48,150 --> 00:56:50,590
All right. Let's have it your way.

929
00:56:50,710 --> 00:56:54,750
Fate rules our lives.
Fate caused us to be together now.

930
00:56:55,670 --> 00:56:59,710
You think it's our fate to be lovers,
and I think it's our fate to be apart.

931
00:57:00,230 --> 00:57:02,270
Let's see. Right now.

932
00:57:03,870 --> 00:57:05,390
That's endearing.

933
00:57:06,270 --> 00:57:08,990
You want to toss a coin
to see if we become lovers.

934
00:57:09,150 --> 00:57:11,510
I forget. Did Romeo and Juliet do that...

935
00:57:11,670 --> 00:57:13,790
...or did they just flip baseball cards?

936
00:57:13,910 --> 00:57:16,390
- Are you backing out?
- I'm not backing out.

937
00:57:16,510 --> 00:57:18,870
All right, then. Heads, we become lovers.

938
00:57:18,950 --> 00:57:21,870
Tails, I'll go away. You'll never see me again.

939
00:57:22,470 --> 00:57:23,670
You can blame it on fate.

940
00:57:23,750 --> 00:57:26,390
I don't have to blame what I decide on anything.

941
00:57:26,510 --> 00:57:30,230
So put your sentimentality to the test
and toss the damn thing.

942
00:57:31,510 --> 00:57:34,270
- But I read the coin.
- You can read the coin.

943
00:57:36,110 --> 00:57:37,950
Toss it over here by me.

944
00:57:40,670 --> 00:57:42,070
You ready?

945
00:57:42,550 --> 00:57:43,670
Toss it.

946
00:58:15,190 --> 00:58:16,150
So...

947
00:58:20,750 --> 00:58:22,030
What is it?

948
00:58:23,310 --> 00:58:26,070
- It's tails.
- Right. Seriously, what is it?

949
00:58:27,190 --> 00:58:28,470
It's tails.

950
00:58:32,430 --> 00:58:33,590
You sure?

951
00:58:37,910 --> 00:58:41,430
Don't you think I know the difference
between heads and tails?

952
00:58:42,950 --> 00:58:43,950
Fate.

953
00:58:52,270 --> 00:58:54,550
<i>"She looked enchanting in her black dress.</i>

954
00:58:55,630 --> 00:58:57,510
"Her neck was enchanting.

955
00:58:58,190 --> 00:58:59,990
"Her hair was enchanting.

956
00:59:00,070 --> 00:59:02,230
"Her visage was enchanting. "

957
00:59:02,630 --> 00:59:04,430
This chick was pretty enchanting.

958
00:59:04,790 --> 00:59:06,070
Apparently.

959
00:59:07,350 --> 00:59:11,150
- Nina, can I ask you a question?
- I've been blind since I was 10 months old.

960
00:59:12,030 --> 00:59:14,230
- No, I wasn't gonna ask you that.
- Yes, you were.

961
00:59:14,310 --> 00:59:17,470
No, I was gonna ask you
if you were seeing somebody.

962
00:59:17,790 --> 00:59:19,150
No.

963
00:59:19,270 --> 00:59:21,230
No, I'm not seeing anybody.

964
00:59:24,110 --> 00:59:25,230
Stupid Jesus.

965
00:59:25,310 --> 00:59:27,310
- No, you're not.
- I am. I shouldn't have...

966
00:59:27,430 --> 00:59:28,910
No, I was just making a joke.

967
00:59:29,030 --> 00:59:31,470
You know what I meant.
Are you going out with somebody?

968
00:59:31,550 --> 00:59:32,510
No.

969
00:59:37,790 --> 00:59:40,030
- What?
- Take me home.

970
00:59:40,150 --> 00:59:42,390
- Why? I'm sorry.
- I want to go home. Take me home.

971
00:59:42,470 --> 00:59:44,790
I didn't mean that. I'm...

972
00:59:48,190 --> 00:59:49,190
