Are you all right?

1221
01:21:18,830 --> 01:21:21,430
My mother died last night,
and why wasn't I there?

1222
01:21:21,550 --> 01:21:23,710
- That's not your fault.
- I know.

1223
01:21:24,510 --> 01:21:27,670
I know it isn't, but why do I feel like it is?

1224
01:21:28,470 --> 01:21:29,870
And why do I...

1225
01:21:30,790 --> 01:21:32,710
I feel like I'm being punished...

1226
01:21:33,110 --> 01:21:35,470
...for not being somewhere
that I should have been.

1227
01:21:38,790 --> 01:21:40,550
I feel so lost.

1228
01:21:42,710 --> 01:21:43,790
Hi.

1229
01:21:46,110 --> 01:21:47,990
We should go, sweetheart.

1230
01:22:04,710 --> 01:22:05,990
I gotta go.

1231
01:22:08,510 --> 01:22:09,750
Of course.

1232
01:22:10,430 --> 01:22:12,230
Of course you gotta go.

1233
01:22:54,070 --> 01:22:55,350
You waited.

1234
01:22:56,750 --> 01:22:59,190
You knew that was gonna happen, right?

1235
01:23:01,550 --> 01:23:03,230
I didn't have a clue.

1236
01:23:05,590 --> 01:23:06,870
I never do.

1237
01:23:07,670 --> 01:23:09,430
What are you gonna do?

1238
01:24:11,510 --> 01:24:14,470
- I can't help thinking that this is my fault.
- It's not.

1239
01:24:14,550 --> 01:24:17,630
No. I know, but I keep feeling,
what if I hadn't come here?

1240
01:24:17,750 --> 01:24:20,590
- What if we hadn't...
- You think my mother would still be alive?

1241
01:24:20,710 --> 01:24:21,630
No.

1242
01:24:23,510 --> 01:24:24,950
She adored you.

1243
01:24:26,830 --> 01:24:28,190
You were right, what you said.

1244
01:24:28,310 --> 01:24:30,430
- What did I say?
- About passion.

1245
01:24:30,550 --> 01:24:32,710
About how we run into passion blindly.

1246
01:24:32,790 --> 01:24:36,550
How we lose our perspective,
and, right in the middle of it, real life happens...

1247
01:24:36,630 --> 01:24:38,190
...catches up and changes everything.

1248
01:24:38,270 --> 01:24:39,670
Yes, it does.

1249
01:24:40,310 --> 01:24:43,110
- Everything comes crashing down.
- Like a stone.

1250
01:24:44,230 --> 01:24:45,270
Yeah.

1251
01:24:45,390 --> 01:24:47,790
I feel like a weight's been lifted off my back...

1252
01:24:47,910 --> 01:24:50,510
...'cause I hated feeling about you like that.

1253
01:24:50,710 --> 01:24:51,870
Did you?

1254
01:24:52,230 --> 01:24:55,990
Yeah. It made me feel foolish. Stupid.

1255
01:24:56,950 --> 01:25:00,630
Like someone else was inside me,
saying those things, doing them.

1256
01:25:00,830 --> 01:25:03,310
- And like you said, it can't last, can it?
- No, it can't.

1257
01:25:03,390 --> 01:25:05,590
- Doesn't...
- Doesn't, not at all.

1258
01:25:09,990 --> 01:25:13,390
- I'm so sorry about your mother.
- Thank you.

1259
01:25:14,070 --> 01:25:16,350
- Did you tell Eric?
- About us?

1260
01:25:16,630 --> 01:25:17,950
Yes, about us. What did he say?

1261
01:25:18,070 --> 01:25:22,110
Yes, I did, and he said it's already forgotten.

1262
01:25:25,630 --> 01:25:27,190
See, that's great.

1263
01:25:27,350 --> 01:25:30,910
He can forget
something like that ever happened.

1264
01:25:31,030 --> 01:25:33,230
I wish I could be more like that.

1265
01:25:34,110 --> 01:25:36,230
I wish I could be more controlled.

1266
01:25:36,590 --> 01:25:38,270
I'll see you on Monday.

1267
01:25:49,310 --> 01:25:53,270
I'm leaving in a couple of days.
Probably better like this.

1268
01:25:53,510 --> 01:25:54,950
Yes, much.

1269
01:25:57,110 --> 01:25:59,710
I'm sorry if I messed anything up for you.

1270
01:26:00,350 --> 01:26:02,750
- You didn't.
- You sure?

1271
01:26:10,550 --> 01:26:11,750
Good-bye.

1272
01:26:54,230 --> 01:26:56,190
So, Irene, you saw Estelle?

1273
01:26:56,750 --> 01:26:59,030
Yes. She seemed depressed to me,
at the funeral.

1274
01:27:00,150 --> 01:27:02,550
Yes. She was upset. She seemed upset.

1275
01:27:02,710 --> 01:27:05,110
Hold on a second, honey.
Eric has something to tell us.

1276
01:27:05,270 --> 01:27:08,790
I was gonna say that Anna and I
are flying to Paris to get married.

1277
01:27:11,070 --> 01:27:14,230
- Paris! How romantic.
- That's wonderful.

1278
01:27:14,390 --> 01:27:17,430
- Congratulations, you guys.
- I'm happy for you, darling.

1279
01:27:17,590 --> 01:27:20,230
- Thanks, Dad.
- When are you guys heading out?

1280
01:27:20,310 --> 01:27:23,030
- Sunday.
- Sunday? That soon?

1281
01:27:27,270 --> 01:27:28,630
Does anybody want more coffee?

1282
01:27:28,910 --> 01:27:30,150
I'll have some.

1283
01:28:10,990 --> 01:28:13,390
Why did you want to see me?
I have to go and pack.

1284
01:28:13,510 --> 01:28:16,190
<i>Jesus finished reading Anna Karenina to me.</i>

1285
01:28:16,350 --> 01:28:19,670
- You didn't ask me here to tell me that.
- Mother was wrong.

1286
01:28:19,990 --> 01:28:22,670
It's not a great love story.
It's a stupid love story.

1287
01:28:22,830 --> 01:28:24,070
- Is it?
- Yes.

1288
01:28:24,150 --> 01:28:25,830
She throws herself under a train.

1289
01:28:25,910 --> 01:28:26,870
I've read it.

1290
01:28:26,990 --> 01:28:30,510
But even after she did it,
she realizes she made a mistake.

1291
01:28:30,710 --> 01:28:33,590
She tries to get out, but it's too late.

1292
01:28:33,870 --> 01:28:35,350
What's your point?

1293
01:28:35,470 --> 01:28:38,790
- Don't go to Paris.
- And what should I do instead?

1294
01:28:38,910 --> 01:28:41,630
- Find Danny. Go with him.
- You're being childish!

1295
01:28:41,750 --> 01:28:44,470
I'm not being childish. You don't love Eric.

1296
01:28:44,990 --> 01:28:48,430
- Yes, I do, in my way.
- And what way is that?

1297
01:28:48,990 --> 01:28:52,230
I can't explain it to you right now.
There are other things involved.

1298
01:28:52,310 --> 01:28:56,110
- What things?
- Karen, Father, Billy, you.

1299
01:28:56,390 --> 01:28:59,430
- Don't hide behind us, Anna.
- What do you mean, hide behind you?

1300
01:28:59,550 --> 01:29:01,110
We don't need you.

1301
01:29:01,750 --> 01:29:02,870
You don't need me?

1302
01:29:05,510 --> 01:29:07,470
How can you say that to me?

1303
01:29:07,750 --> 01:29:10,190
My God!
I have nursed you all when you were sick!

1304
01:29:10,390 --> 01:29:12,910
I've given you money.
I've taken care of your children.

1305
01:29:13,030 --> 01:29:14,550
I've lied for you!

1306
01:29:15,030 --> 01:29:17,710
And you just stand there
and say you don't need me?

1307
01:29:17,790 --> 01:29:19,310
Because we don't.

1308
01:29:20,310 --> 01:29:22,710
Look, it's not the same. Everything's changed.

1309
01:29:22,830 --> 01:29:25,910
- What? What's changed?
- Everything. Everyone.

1310
01:29:26,550 --> 01:29:31,190
Danny's love for you is so enormous,
it spilled over onto everyone else.

1311
01:29:31,830 --> 01:29:33,670
He's changed you, too...

1312
01:29:34,270 --> 01:29:37,190
...only you're the last one to notice it.

1313
01:29:42,030 --> 01:29:44,150
It's the mosaic Danny worked on.

1314
01:29:47,950 --> 01:29:50,230
Jesus described it to me yesterday.

1315
01:30:00,110 --> 01:30:01,470
You love him.

1316
01:30:06,190 --> 01:30:07,870
Of course I love him.

1317
01:30:09,230 --> 01:30:10,670
Of course I do.

1318
01:30:12,710 --> 01:30:14,110
But I'm scared.

1319
01:30:20,230 --> 01:30:22,350
I've been scared my whole life.

1320
01:30:23,830 --> 01:30:25,310
It's only now...

1321
01:30:26,150 --> 01:30:28,310
...that I'm in love, I'm not scared.

1322
01:31:03,830 --> 01:31:05,790
- Where did he say he was going?
- I don't know.

1323
01:31:05,910 --> 01:31:07,870
- She took my Ring Ding.
- Did not!

1324
01:31:07,990 --> 01:31:10,470
- Did you take his Ring Ding?
- Karen, please, think.

1325
01:31:12,270 --> 01:31:14,510
Atlanta. He said there was work there.

1326
01:31:14,590 --> 01:31:17,830
- Did he say how he was getting there?
- The train, I think.

1327
01:31:17,950 --> 01:31:19,230
Thank you.

1328
01:31:21,710 --> 01:31:23,790
Listen, you don't want that.

1329
01:31:23,870 --> 01:31:25,270
The sugar's poison.

1330
01:31:25,990 --> 01:31:29,390
You know, they injected a rat 20 times a day...

1331
01:31:29,470 --> 01:31:30,990
...for five years with this stuff.

1332
01:31:31,110 --> 01:31:32,830
Do you know what it died of?

1333
01:31:58,510 --> 01:32:00,910
I need to find the train to Atlanta.

1334
01:32:38,270 --> 01:32:39,790
What are you doing here?

1335
01:32:39,870 --> 01:32:42,030
- You were right.
- What about?

1336
01:32:42,110 --> 01:32:44,510
About everything. About us. I was wrong.

1337
01:32:44,630 --> 01:32:45,790
- No, you weren't.
- Yes, I was.

1338
01:32:45,910 --> 01:32:47,390
No, you weren't.

1339
01:32:47,790 --> 01:32:50,350
Look, my train's leaving. I've gotta go.

1340
01:32:51,110 --> 01:32:53,190
- No. Listen.
- I'm really sorry.

1341
01:32:53,310 --> 01:32:55,510
Listen. My mother was right.

1342
01:32:55,550 --> 01:32:58,830
She said it was my turn
to do something extraordinary and I'm doing it.

1343
01:32:58,910 --> 01:33:01,390
I'm here at a train station
in the middle of the night...

1344
01:33:01,510 --> 01:33:04,390
...like a character in a Russian novel,
and I'm begging you.

1345
01:33:04,470 --> 01:33:07,350
- To do what?
- To take me with you.

1346
01:33:08,350 --> 01:33:09,990
You don't know where I'm going.

1347
01:33:10,070 --> 01:33:13,070
- I don't care!
- No. Listen to yourself.

1348
01:33:13,150 --> 01:33:15,550
This is passion. Passion talking.

1349
01:33:15,790 --> 01:33:19,030
I know all about it. Believe me. And it feels fun.

1350
01:33:19,150 --> 01:33:22,990
You do these stupid things like this.
But in the end, it doesn't work.

1351
01:33:23,190 --> 01:33:24,630
It won't last.

1352
01:33:25,790 --> 01:33:27,350
What have I done to you?

1353
01:33:28,310 --> 01:33:29,350
What?

1354
01:33:30,030 --> 01:33:31,830
You sound just like me.

1355
01:33:33,870 --> 01:33:35,470
- Is that bad?
- Yes.

1356
01:33:36,430 --> 01:33:37,830
It's terrible.

1357
01:33:40,150 --> 01:33:41,710
- I'm sorry.
- Wait.

1358
01:33:42,470 --> 01:33:45,630
We'll do it your way then. We'll let fate decide.

1359
01:33:50,550 --> 01:33:51,990
Is that a real coin?

1360
01:33:52,670 --> 01:33:54,990
Of course it's a real coin. Why wouldn't it be?

1361
01:33:55,070 --> 01:33:56,550
No. No reason.

1362
01:33:56,790 --> 01:34:00,950
All right, heads, I go with you,
and tails, you can go away...

1363
01:34:01,030 --> 01:34:03,470
...and I'll never bother you again. Deal?

1364
01:34:05,670 --> 01:34:07,510
All right, deal.

1365
01:34:08,110 --> 01:34:11,830
- But I read the coin.
- All right. You read the coin.

1366
01:34:17,590 --> 01:34:20,510
- Okay, you ready?
- Toss it.

1367
01:34:40,310 --> 01:34:41,870
What is it?

1368
01:34:43,950 --> 01:34:45,830
Aren't you gonna read it?

1369
01:34:48,990 --> 01:34:50,110
It's heads.

1370
01:34:59,150 --> 01:35:00,630
God, I love you.

1371
01:35:32,230 --> 01:35:33,990
You did good, partner.

1372
01:35:34,990 --> 01:35:37,550
Mom would have gotten a kick out of that.

1373
01:35:37,670 --> 01:35:39,350
I'm gonna marry her.

1374
01:35:40,950 --> 01:35:43,990
Well, there's lot easier ways to meet a woman...

1375
01:35:44,230 --> 01:35:46,270
...especially for the woman.

